definition.value: A service provided online or by the internet.
A service for matchmaking between potential couples, with a view toward romance and/or marriage between them.

A company that provides specific mechanisms (generally websites or applications) for online dating through the use of Internet-connected personal computers or mobile devices. Such companies offer a wide variety of unmoderated matchmaking services, most of which are profile-based.
Online dating services primarily used for the purposes of heterosexual dating.
Online dating services primarily used for the purposes of dating for gay persons.

An underground feminist punk movement that began in the early 1990s in Washington state (particularly Olympia) and the greater Pacific Northwest. It also had origins in Washington, D.C., and spread to at least 26 countries. It is a subcultural movement that combines feminist consciousness and punk style and politics. It is often associated with third-wave feminism, which is sometimes seen as having grown out of the Riot Grrrl movement.
A crime in which an offender or perpetrator uses or threatens to use force upon a victim.
Unlawful sexual acts or behaviors.

What is and isn't considered a sex crime varies greatly from culture to culture and from time period to time period. For this reason, individual instances which may be considered sex crimes (such as forced prostitution, sexual assault, incestual abuse, and forced marriage, among others) are listed elsewhere.
A prejudice-motivated crime which occurs when a perpetrator targets a victim because of their membership (or perceived membership) in a certain group.
A prejudice-motivated crime which occurs when a perpetrator targets a victim because of their membership (or perceived membership) in the Jewish community.
A prejudice-motivated crime which occurs when a perpetrator targets a victim because of their membership (or perceived membership) in a particular race.
A form of political violence expressly motivated by racial hatred and race conflict.
A form of political violence expressly motivated by hatred of Black persons and race conflict aimed at Black persons.
A prejudice-motivated crime which occurs when a perpetrator targets a victim because of their membership (or perceived membership) in the transgender community.
A prejudice-motivated crime which occurs when a perpetrator targets a victim because of their membership (or perceived membership) in the gay male community.
A prejudice-motivated crime which occurs when a perpetrator targets a victim because of their membership (or perceived membership) in the lesbian community.
Hegemonic masculinity is a practice that legitimizes men's dominant position in society and justifies the subordination of women, and other marginalized ways of being a man.
A gendered society in which the masculine is considered dominant to the feminine.
A gendered society in which the masculine is considered submissive to the feminine.
A gendered society in which the feminine is considered dominant to the masculine.
A gendered society in which the feminine is considered submissive to the masculine.
Female gender roles classified by power structure or roles.
Male gender roles classified by power structure or roles.
Male gender roles classified by the gender identity of the individual.
Female gender roles classified by the gender identity of the individual.
Traditional masculinity displayed by a person with a female gender identity.
Traditional masculinity displayed by a person with a male gender identity.
Traditional femininity displayed by a person with a male gender identity.
Traditional femininity displayed by a person with a female gender identity.
Male gender roles classified by sexuality.
Female gender roles classified by sexuality.
The subculture of gay men who self-identify with what is considered to be traditional, heterosexual (male) masculinity.
The subculture of gay women who self-identify with what is considered to be traditional, heterosexual (female) femininity.
Heterosexual women who self-identify with what is considered to be a traditional femininity.
Heterosexual men who self-identify with what is considered to be a traditional masculinity.

Stereotypically masculine gender roles that restrict the kinds of emotions allowable for boys and men to express, including social expectations that men seek to be dominant (the "alpha male") and limit their emotional range primarily to expressions of anger.
Male gender roles classified by relative role importance in the individual.
Female gender roles classified by relative role importance in the individual.
A psychological term for the absence of female stereotypical traits.
A psychological term for the exaggeration of female stereotypical behavior.
A psychological term for the exaggeration of male stereotypical behavior, such as an emphasis on physical strength, aggression, and sexuality.

A psychological term for the absence of male stereotypical traits. For example, it is the absence of the de-emphasising of feelings and relationships. Oftentimes, individuals who exhibit hypomasculine traits display unmasculine professional or physical characteristics that deviate from the norm.

The concept that transgender women are women trapped in men's bodies. This idea has been interpreted in many senses, as a female mind, spirit, soul, personality, etc., as well as in more literal senses such as having a female brain structure; it is also a psychological narrative, that is, a self-description of how some transgender women see themselves, or of how they may portray themselves to qualify for certain medical treatments.

Situational sexual behavior differs from that which the person normally exhibits, due to a social environment that in some way permits, encourages, or compels the behavior in question. This can also include situations where a person's usual sexual behavior may not be possible, so rather than not engaging in sexual activity at all, they may engage in different sexual behaviors.
Primarily heterosexual, but open to taking part in a limited amount of homosexual activity.
Primarily homosexual, but with a limited amount of attraction to the opposite sex, or willingness to take part in a heterosexual activity.
The assumption that being queer means that that person is a gay man; also the privilege of gay men as normative within the queer community.
Any therapeutic technique which uses hormones in medical treatment.
Various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level.
Any therapeutic procedure in which medications are given to replace an absence of a given hormone or hormones.

A form of hormone therapy in which androgens, often testosterone, are replaced. ART is often prescribed to counter the effects of male hypogonadism. It typically involves the administration of testosterone through injections, skin creams, patches, gels, or subcutaneous pellets.
